+- [ ] Create `before-after-gallery.js` with `decorate(block)` export
+- [ ] Implement config parsing from block rows (camelCase keys: tabs → images)
+- [ ] Build tab/toggle navigation with ARIA tablist pattern (`role="tablist"`, `role="tab"`, `aria-selected`, `aria-controls`)
+- [ ] Build thumbnail grid with click-to-select behavior (show selected slider, hide others, toggle `.is-active`)
+- [ ] Build main before/after slider reusing `--compare-position` CSS custom property pattern
+- [ ] Implement drag handle: `pointerdown` + `pointermove` + `pointerup` event handling (replaces separate mouse/touch)
+- [ ] Implement keyboard support: ArrowLeft/ArrowRight on slider handle, Tab between thumbnails
+- [ ] Add authored prompt text overlay that hides after first drag interaction
+- [ ] Wire tab switching: swap thumbnail set + reset slider to first image pair
+- [ ] Wire thumbnail click: swap main slider before/after images + update labels
+- [ ] Render before/after labels and attribution text from authored fields
+- [ ] Apply `anchorId` to block wrapper and `analyticsId` as `data-analytics`
+- [ ] Ensure first tab and first thumbnail are active on load
+
+### Phase 3: CSS Implementation
+- [ ] Create `before-after-gallery.css` with all styles
+- [ ] Style tab bar: horizontal button strip with brand-color active state (matching `risa-tabs-images` and `toggle-pictures-slider`)
+- [ ] Style toggle variant: two-button toggle with active highlight (pill shape)
+- [ ] Style main slider container: `position: relative; overflow: hidden; user-select: none`
+- [ ] Style after image layer: `display: block; width: 100%`
+- [ ] Style before image layer: `position: absolute; inset: 0; width: var(--compare-position); overflow: hidden`
+- [ ] Style handle: 4px white line + 40px circular indicator with swap arrows SVG icon
+- [ ] Style thumbnail grid: CSS grid `repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr))` — 4-col desktop, 2-col mobile
+- [ ] Style thumbnail active state: border highlight (`.is-active`)
+- [ ] Style thumbnail labels: positioned at bottom with semi-transparent overlay
+- [ ] Style thumbnail sublabel: smaller text for clearance percentage
+- [ ] Style drag prompt: centered overlay text, pointer-events none, fades out
+- [ ] Style before/after text labels: positioned absolute inside slider
+- [ ] Add `prefers-reduced-motion` fallback
+- [ ] Add mobile responsive breakpoint (thumbnails 2-col, handle 44px touch target)
+
+### Phase 4: Brand Overrides & Build
+- [ ] Create `block-config.js` (empty scaffold)
+- [ ] Create brand override directories (abbvie, botox, rinvoq) with scaffolded `_before-after-gallery.css` + `block-config.js`
+- [ ] Run `gulp createBrandCSS` to compile brand override CSS
+- [ ] Run ESLint on JS
+- [ ] Run Stylelint on CSS
+
+### Phase 5: Testing & Validation
+- [ ] Inject test block via browser DevTools on localhost:3000 homepage
+- [ ] Verify two tabs render with correct labels
+- [ ] Verify tab switching swaps thumbnail grid and resets slider
+- [ ] Verify thumbnail click swaps main slider images and updates labels
+- [ ] Verify slider drag works (mouse + touch via PointerEvents + keyboard arrows)
+- [ ] Verify toggle variant renders correctly (pill buttons)
+- [ ] Verify ARIA attributes: tablist, tab, slider roles with correct aria-selected/aria-controls/aria-valuenow
+- [ ] Verify mobile layout: thumbnails 2-col grid, slider full-width, handle touch-friendly (44px)
+- [ ] Verify prompt text appears on load and hides after first drag
+- [ ] Verify `prefers-reduced-motion` disables transitions
+
+## Risk & Complexity Notes
+- **HIGH complexity** — nested repeating UE model (tabs → images), three interaction systems (tabs, thumbnails, slider), responsive layout
+- SkyriziHCP has 10 patients per tab (20 sliders total) — the EDS block only renders ONE slider at a time and swaps images on thumbnail click, so performance is much better than the source site's 20 pre-rendered sliders
+- Nested `model` fields require careful UE authoring UX — two levels of repeating content (tabs containing image sets)
+- PointerEvents API used instead of separate mouse/touch handlers — cleaner, better browser support
+- No external libraries — pure CSS + vanilla JS
+- Brand-specific styling (SkyriziHCP navy/arctic theme vs Rinvoq DTC purple) handled entirely via CSS custom properties (`--brand-primary`, `--color-accent`)
+
+---
+
+*This plan requires Execute mode for implementation.*
